'''Salah Zakaria Hassan''' (born 24 April 1999) is a Qatari professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] and the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Club career==
Zakaria began his professional career with [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]] in 2019. In January 2021 he joined [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.besoccer.com/player/transfers/salah-zakaria-hassan-846025 | title=Salah Zakaria transfers | date= | accessdate=2023-08-17}}</ref>

==International career==
In August 2022, Zakaria made his first appearance for the Qatar national team against [[Jamaica]]. The match ended 1-1.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/08/26/world/friendlies/qatar/jamaica/3932876/ | title=Qatar vs. Jamaica 1-1 | date=2022-08-26 | accessdate=2022-10-14}}</ref>

